<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Retain meta data (EXIF, XMP, IPTC) of the original image</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div class="content"><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select if the meta data of the original image is to be retained.<br>
Examples of meta data are description texts, geo data (GPS), date and time.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Activated</strong> = The original image’s meta data is retained for scaled images of this size.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> To optimise load time and data volume, it may be advisable to not retain meta data particularly for preview images.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div></td>
